                "name": "Jon Mixon",
                "href": "/profile/Jon-Mixon-1"
            },
            "answer_text": "In a small Ohio town roughly 25 miles from me, there are some biracial children whose mother apparently left the church, bore them and then returned later in life. They are, sadly, a minor curiosity in that town and at least the oldest (to my understanding) has left the church and the area due to prejudice and the lack of opportunities. The Amish nearly always marry within their faith when they remain in their church. And the ones who leave the church often retain many of the sect\u2019s attitudes towards minorities which aren\u2019t progressive to put it very nicely. Additionally, the Amish church doesn\u2019t proselytize so they don\u2019t attract new members from the outside. If they did, again with the social views held by the current members, it\u2019s unlikely that they would seek out Black or African American acolytes as that would result in intermarriage and thus \u201cInterbreeding.\u201d ",
